  "text": "The HotSpot JIT compilation pipeline consists of five key components located in src/hotspot/share/:\n\n1. **CompileBroker** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compileBroker.hpp, line 165): The central coordinator that manages all compilation requests. It maintains compile queues for C1 and C2, assigns compilation IDs, and orchestrates the compilation process. The class CompileBroker (defined as AllStatic) contains static methods like compile_method() and manages compiler threads, compile queues (_c1_compile_queue, _c2_compile_queue), and compiler instances (AbstractCompiler* _compilers[2]).\n\n2. **CompilerThread** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compilerThread.hpp, line 42): A specialized JavaThread that executes compilation tasks. Each CompilerThread carries compilation state including ciEnv, CompileLog, CompileTask, CompileQueue, and a reference to its AbstractCompiler. The thread runs in a loop, pulling tasks from its compile queue and invoking compilation.\n\n3. **Compiler (C1)** (src/hotspot/share/c1/c1_Compiler.hpp, line 34): The first-tier JIT compiler that derives from AbstractCompiler. It provides fast compilation with minimal optimization, generating machine code suitable for frequently executed methods at lower optimization cost.\n\n4. **C2Compiler** (src/hotspot/share/opto/c2compiler.hpp, line 36): The optimizing second-tier JIT compiler that also derives from AbstractCompiler. It performs aggressive optimizations including escape analysis, method inlining, and graph reduction, targeting hot code paths requiring maximum performance.\n\n5. **AbstractCompiler** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/abstractCompiler.hpp, line 75): The base class for all compiler implementations (C1, C2, and JVMCI). It defines the compiler lifecycle, state management, intrinsic support queries, and the compile_method() virtual interface. Both C1 and C2 inherit from this class, implementing the pure virtual compile_method() method and initialize() method.\n\nThe compilation pipeline flow: CompileBroker receives compilation requests and queues them in appropriate compile queues based on compilation level. CompilerThreads (one or more per tier) dequeue tasks, compile them through their assigned Compiler instance (C1 or C2), and produce optimized nmethods."
}

